<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="587" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1368,2043]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,502,1511,1538]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Diagnosis (partial, male).</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[655,755,1512,1538]" class="Arachnida" family="Nemesiidae" genus="Brachythele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="media">
<emphasis box="[655,755,1512,1538]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">B. media</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be similar to males of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[1142,1253,1512,1538]" class="Arachnida" family="Nemesiidae" genus="Brachythele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denieri">
<emphasis box="[1142,1253,1512,1538]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">B. denieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Drensky, P." pageId="4" pageNumber="587" pagination="259 - 280" refId="ref3556" refString="Drensky, P. (1937) Faounata na paiatzite (Araneae) w Beulgaria. Podrazred Mygalomorphae: semeystwa Ctenizidae i Atypidae. Izvestiya na Tsarskite Prirodonauchni Instituti v Sofia, 10, 259 - 280." type="journal article" year="1937">Drensky 1937</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dalmas, 1921)" baseAuthorityName="Dalmas" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[271,584,1548,1574]" class="Arachnida" family="Nemesiidae" genus="Brachythele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varrialei">
<emphasis box="[271,288,1549,1574]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[303,401,1548,1574]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">varrialei</emphasis>
(Dalmas, 1921)
</taxonomicName>
, by the characteristic gradually tapering embolus lacking any embolic keels (
<figureCitation box="[159,289,1584,1611]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-28@6.[151,1436,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–25. Brachythele media (22–23 NHML, 24–25 SMF), male palp. 22 prolateral; 23 ventral; 24 retrolateral, 25 proventral. Scale 0.5 mm." pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Figs 22–25</figureCitation>
). Males can be distinguished from those of the former species by several characters, such as a less swollen palpal tibia, slightly shorter embolus, a noticeably shorter tibial spur with narrower and longer megaspines (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[253,1334,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Brachythele media, male (SMF). 16 habitus, dorsal, 17 carapace; 18 sternum; 19 tibia I, ventral; 20 spinnerets, ventral; 21 tibia I, lateral. Scale 16—2 mm, 17–18—1 mm, 19–21—0.5 mm." pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Figs 19, 21</figureCitation>
cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lazarov, S. &amp; Deltshev, C. &amp; Blagoev, G." box="[263,490,1656,1682]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" pagination="3 - 28" refId="ref3736" refString="Lazarov, S., Deltshev, C. &amp; Blagoev, G. (2001) The spiders (Araneae) of Sashtinska Sredna Gora Mountain (Bulgaria). Faunistic and zoogeographical analysis. Acta Zoologica Bulgarica, 53, 3 - 28." type="journal article" year="2001">
Lazarov 
<emphasis box="[361,410,1656,1682]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">et al</emphasis>
., 2001
</bibRefCitation>
, figs. 3–4), and from the latter—by the aspinose cymbium and the shape of the distal portion of embolus which is less curved and not dilated at the apex (
<figureCitation box="[932,1065,1692,1719]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-28@6.[151,1436,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–25. Brachythele media (22–23 NHML, 24–25 SMF), male palp. 22 prolateral; 23 ventral; 24 retrolateral, 25 proventral. Scale 0.5 mm." pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Figs 22–25</figureCitation>
), while, in males of 
<emphasis box="[1299,1436,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dalmas" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[1299,1432,1692,1718]" class="Arachnida" family="Nemesiidae" genus="Brachythele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varrialei">B. varrialei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the cymbium bears spines and the embolus is slightly twisted and bears a certainly flattened and broadened tip (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Raven, R. J." box="[151,296,1764,1791]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" pagination="1 - 180" refId="ref3983" refString="Raven, R. J. (1985) The spider infraorder Mygalomorphae (Araneae): cladistics and systematics. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 182, 1 - 180." type="journal article" year="1985">Raven, 1985</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 89).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="590" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1368,2043]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,365,1800,1826]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Redescription</emphasis>
(male/SMF). Measurements: Total length 12.50; carapace length 5.44, width 4.26; sternum length 2.57, width 2.11; labium length 0.53, width 0.95; maxilla length 1.94; abdomen length (including spinnerets) 6.50, width 3.85; PLS length 0.63, diameter 0.27; PLE length 1.96 (0.93, 0.54, 0.49), maximal diameter 0.51; Palp, length of segments: femur 2.42, patella 1.09, tibia 1.82, cymbium 0.93, bulbus length 1.50. Leg measurements: Leg I—12.96 (3.89, 2.13, 2.42, 2.69, 1.83), Leg II—12.22 (3.62, 2.01, 2.29, 2.48, 1.82), Leg III—11.57 (3.38, 1.64, 2.04, 2.88, 1.63), Leg IV—16.11 (4.40, 2.19, 3.62, 4.03, 1.87). Eye diameters. ALE 0.32, AME 0.18, PLE 0.25, PME 0.15. AME–AME 0.15, AME–ALE 0.13, ALE–PLE 0.08, PME–PME 0.41, PME–PLE 0.06.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="5" pageNumber="588" startId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[253,1334,181,1877]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1943,2004]" pageId="5" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,342,1943,1967]" pageId="5" pageNumber="588">FIGURES 16–21.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[349,542,1944,1968]" class="Arachnida" family="Nemesiidae" genus="Brachythele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="media">
<emphasis box="[349,542,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="588">Brachythele media</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male (SMF). 16 habitus, dorsal, 17 carapace; 18 sternum; 19 tibia I, ventral; 20 spinnerets, ventral; 21 tibia I, lateral. Scale 16—2 mm, 17–18—1 mm, 19–21—0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption pageId="6" pageNumber="589" startId="6.[151,264,1897,1921]" targetBox="[151,1436,182,1873]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1897,1957]" pageId="6" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,343,1897,1921]" pageId="6" pageNumber="589">FIGURES 22–25.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[351,544,1897,1921]" class="Arachnida" family="Nemesiidae" genus="Brachythele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="media">
<emphasis box="[351,544,1897,1921]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="589">Brachythele media</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(22–23 NHML, 24–25 SMF), male palp. 22 prolateral; 23 ventral; 24 retrolateral, 25 proventral. Scale 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">
Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[357,434,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[253,1334,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Brachythele media, male (SMF). 16 habitus, dorsal, 17 carapace; 18 sternum; 19 tibia I, ventral; 20 spinnerets, ventral; 21 tibia I, lateral. Scale 16—2 mm, 17–18—1 mm, 19–21—0.5 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Fig 16</figureCitation>
. Color. Carapace medium brownish orange, with darker radial stripes and lighter lateral margins (
<figureCitation box="[256,334,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[253,1334,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Brachythele media, male (SMF). 16 habitus, dorsal, 17 carapace; 18 sternum; 19 tibia I, ventral; 20 spinnerets, ventral; 21 tibia I, lateral. Scale 16—2 mm, 17–18—1 mm, 19–21—0.5 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Fig 17</figureCitation>
). Legs lighter than carapace. Sternum, labium, maxillae and coxae light yellowish orange. Sternal sigilla contrasting and well-visible, small, widely oval and submarginal (
<figureCitation box="[984,1064,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[253,1334,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Brachythele media, male (SMF). 16 habitus, dorsal, 17 carapace; 18 sternum; 19 tibia I, ventral; 20 spinnerets, ventral; 21 tibia I, lateral. Scale 16—2 mm, 17–18—1 mm, 19–21—0.5 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Fig 18</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae reddish brown. Abdomen light greyish brown, dorsally with darker chestnut brown pattern consisting of large median spot and few incomplete and diffuse paired lateral chevrons (
<figureCitation box="[684,761,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[253,1334,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Brachythele media, male (SMF). 16 habitus, dorsal, 17 carapace; 18 sternum; 19 tibia I, ventral; 20 spinnerets, ventral; 21 tibia I, lateral. Scale 16—2 mm, 17–18—1 mm, 19–21—0.5 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Fig 16</figureCitation>
). Spinnerets uniformly pale greyish brown (
<figureCitation box="[1255,1333,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[253,1334,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Brachythele media, male (SMF). 16 habitus, dorsal, 17 carapace; 18 sternum; 19 tibia I, ventral; 20 spinnerets, ventral; 21 tibia I, lateral. Scale 16—2 mm, 17–18—1 mm, 19–21—0.5 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Fig 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Eyes. Eye region noticeably elevated. Anterior eye row procurved, posterior one, as seen from the dorsal side, slightly recurved. AME, PLE, and PME about equal in size, ALE considerably larger.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">
Other somatic characters. Carapace dorsally covered with fine dark and silver hairs. Fovea deep and recurved. Chelicerae with 9 promarginal teeth and 3 moderately small mesobasal denticles. Dorsally covered with long, weak, dense hairs. Maxillae with 20–25 very small cuspules in the prolateral basal part (
<figureCitation box="[1074,1151,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[253,1334,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Brachythele media, male (SMF). 16 habitus, dorsal, 17 carapace; 18 sternum; 19 tibia I, ventral; 20 spinnerets, ventral; 21 tibia I, lateral. Scale 16—2 mm, 17–18—1 mm, 19–21—0.5 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Fig 18</figureCitation>
). Tibia I preapically with proventral spur bearing 2 megaspines (
<figureCitation box="[585,715,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,181,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[253,1334,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Brachythele media, male (SMF). 16 habitus, dorsal, 17 carapace; 18 sternum; 19 tibia I, ventral; 20 spinnerets, ventral; 21 tibia I, lateral. Scale 16—2 mm, 17–18—1 mm, 19–21—0.5 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Figs 19, 21</figureCitation>
). Scopula: distal and entire on metatarsi I–II, entire on tarsi I–II; widely divided and mixed with setae on tarsus III; sparse and rudimentary on tarsus IV. Trichobothria 
<quantity box="[1280,1350,547,573]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.905" metricValueMax="2.032" metricValueMin="1.778" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" unit="in" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8 in</quantity>
each of two rows on tibiae, 12–14 on metatarsi, 12–13 on tarsi. Paired claws with 6–7 teeth in each row.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">
Palp (
<figureCitation box="[264,396,618,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-28@6.[151,1436,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–25. Brachythele media (22–23 NHML, 24–25 SMF), male palp. 22 prolateral; 23 ventral; 24 retrolateral, 25 proventral. Scale 0.5 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Figs 22–25</figureCitation>
). Femur, patella, and cymbium spineless. Tibia with 2 long dorsal and 15–20 slightly shorter ventral spiniform setae. Bulbus pear-shaped, its embolic portion narrow, slightly curved, and gradually tapered.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,753]" box="[199,843,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Female.</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation author="Ausserer, A." box="[346,527,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" pagination="117 - 224" refId="ref3437" refString="Ausserer, A. (1871) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Arachniden-Familie der Territelariae Thorell (Mygalidae Autor). Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 21, 117 - 224. [incl. unpubl. manuscript by Doleschall]" type="journal article" year="1871">Ausserer (1871)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Naumova, M. &amp; Hristovski, S. &amp; Hristov, G. H." box="[582,839,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" pagination="503 - 511" refId="ref3822" refString="Naumova, M., Hristovski, S. &amp; Hristov, G. H. (2016) Spiders (Arachnida: Araneae) from Prespa National Park, Albania. Acta Zoologica Bulgarica, 68 (4), 503 - 511." type="journal article" year="2016">
Naumova 
<emphasis box="[698,747,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="590" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,753]" box="[199,1043,726,753]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,726,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,451,727,753]" name="Albania" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Albania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[462,544,727,753]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Croatia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[599,697,727,753]" name="Slovenia" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Slovenia</collectingCountry>
(World Spider Catalog, 2021).
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1108,1657,1682]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" startId="7.[151,264,1657,1681]" targetBox="[151,1427,781,1634]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1108,1657,1682]" box="[151,1108,1657,1682]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,340,1657,1681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">FIGURES 26–27.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zonstein" authorityYear="2007" box="[346,566,1657,1681]" class="Arachnida" family="Nemesiidae" genus="Brachythele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bentzieni">
<emphasis box="[346,566,1657,1681]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Brachythele bentzieni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male palp. 26 ventral; 27 retrolateral. Scale 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1728,1934]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1728,1754]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">Notes.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[418,516,1728,1754]" class="Arachnida" family="Nemesiidae" genus="Brachythele" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="media">
<emphasis box="[418,435,1728,1753]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[448,516,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="590">media</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first depicted (including figures of the habitus, the palp, and the tibial spur) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Polenec, A." box="[151,325,1764,1790]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" pagination="367 - 377" refId="ref3941" refString="Polenec, A. (1978) Zusammensetzung und Besonderheiten der Epigaischen Spinnenfauna des Seslerio-Ostryetum am Berge Slavnik (1028 m) (Nord-Istrien, Jugoslawien). Symposia of the Zoological Society of London, 42, 367 - 377." type="journal article" year="1978">Polenec (1978)</bibRefCitation>
. These illustrations, however, were not accompanied by a formal text description. This is thus a first full description of the conspecific male. The only morphometric trait provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Polenec, A." box="[1077,1248,1800,1826]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" pagination="367 - 377" refId="ref3941" refString="Polenec, A. (1978) Zusammensetzung und Besonderheiten der Epigaischen Spinnenfauna des Seslerio-Ostryetum am Berge Slavnik (1028 m) (Nord-Istrien, Jugoslawien). Symposia of the Zoological Society of London, 42, 367 - 377." type="journal article" year="1978">Polenec (1978)</bibRefCitation>
is the total male body length: 
<quantity box="[302,385,1835,1862]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
. Both males studied and measured in the course of the current study are 
<quantity box="[1215,1316,1835,1862]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" unit="mm" value="12.5">12.5 mm</quantity>
long. One male was collected by A. Polenec. Since the first Slovenian record by 
<bibRefCitation author="Polenec, A." box="[940,1110,1872,1898]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" pagination="367 - 377" refId="ref3941" refString="Polenec, A. (1978) Zusammensetzung und Besonderheiten der Epigaischen Spinnenfauna des Seslerio-Ostryetum am Berge Slavnik (1028 m) (Nord-Istrien, Jugoslawien). Symposia of the Zoological Society of London, 42, 367 - 377." type="journal article" year="1978">Polenec (1978)</bibRefCitation>
was based on 
<specimenCount box="[1275,1392,1872,1898]" pageId="7" pageNumber="590" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
, we do not know if this author was inaccurate, or if the indicated body length corresponds to another male specimen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
